1
00:00:00,323 --> 00:00:01,769
Previously on One Tree Hill.

2
00:00:01,820 --> 00:00:03,054
I have a right to my daughter.

3
00:00:03,704 --> 00:00:04,641
You’re not getting her.

4
00:00:10,605 --> 00:00:12,029
Petition for annulment?

5
00:00:12,592 --> 00:00:14,250
It’ll be like the marriage never happened.

6
00:00:14,994 --> 00:00:18,167
There’s... no way that he signed this.

7
00:00:18,290 --> 00:00:19,382
It’s over, Haley.

8
00:00:20,994 --> 00:00:21,932
Jake Jagielski.

9
00:00:23,048 --> 00:00:24,744
You have the right to remain silent.

10
00:00:25,747 --> 00:00:26,606
I love you.

11
00:00:27,236 --> 00:00:28,331
I love you, too.

12
00:00:29,042 --> 00:00:29,964
Did we have fun?

13
00:00:30,487 --> 00:00:31,382
You tell me.

14
00:00:37,127 --> 00:00:37,967
It’s okay, Deb...

15
00:00:39,274 --> 00:00:40,441
I’ll be here when you get out.

16
00:00:49,502 --> 00:00:50,930
I’m coming home tomorrow, okay?

17
00:00:51,432 --> 00:00:52,682
Don’t come home, Haley.

18
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:53,593
Nathan...

19
00:00:53,778 --> 00:00:55,170
Coz I don’t want you to.

20
00:01:48,270 --> 00:01:49,847
And Hansel said to Gretel...

21
00:01:51,189 --> 00:01:53,033
let us drop these breadcrumbs...

22
00:01:54,301 --> 00:01:56,443
so that together we find our way home.

23
00:01:57,872 --> 00:02:00,594
Because losing our way would be the most cruel of things.

24
00:02:02,776 --> 00:02:03,518
This year...

25
00:02:04,649 --> 00:02:05,806
I lost my way.

26
00:02:10,727 --> 00:02:13,144
And losing your way on a journey is unfortunate.

27
00:02:14,382 --> 00:02:16,419
But, losing your reason for the journey...

28
00:02:17,317 --> 00:02:18,817
is a fate more cruel.

29
00:02:21,566 --> 00:02:23,394
The journey lasted eight months.

30
00:02:24,408 --> 00:02:26,118
Sometimes I travelled alone...

31
00:02:28,243 --> 00:02:30,557
Sometimes, there were others who took the wheel...

32
00:02:32,170 --> 00:02:33,337
and took my heart.

33
00:02:35,564 --> 00:02:37,439
But when the destination was reached...

34
00:02:38,099 --> 00:02:39,789
it wasn’t me who arrived...

35
00:02:41,586 --> 00:02:42,861
it wasn’t me at all.

36
00:02:55,004 --> 00:02:57,924
And once you lose yourself, you have two choices:

37
00:02:58,024 --> 00:02:58,820
Bye!

38
00:03:03,269 --> 00:03:05,132
Find the person you used to be...

39
00:03:08,737 --> 00:03:10,586
or lose that person completely.

40
00:03:12,352 --> 00:03:15,715
Because, sometimes, you have to step outside of the person you’ve been.

41
00:03:16,376 --> 00:03:18,705
And remember the person you were meant to be.

42
00:03:19,643 --> 00:03:21,098
The person you wanted to be.

43
00:03:22,399 --> 00:03:25,806
- Jimmy, Jimmy, Jimmy...
- The person you are.

44
00:03:27,552 --> 00:03:30,395
Tree Hill student council is pleased to welcome-

45
00:03:30,605 --> 00:03:34,747
No. As president of the student council, I promised you guys a good time...

46
00:03:35,531 --> 00:03:38,177
I’m Brooke Davis and I’m an idiot, but, please welcome-

47
00:03:39,074 --> 00:03:40,961
Jimmy Eat World, that’s a great idea!

48
00:03:41,055 --> 00:03:42,299
Brooke, it’ll probably never happen.

49
00:03:42,413 --> 00:03:46,362
Peyton Elizabeth Sawyer, you got The Wreckers and Pelthead to come and play;

50
00:03:46,421 --> 00:03:48,741
you can totally land Jimmy Eat World and when you do,

51
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:51,679
I promise I won’t break up with you to run off and join their tour.

52
00:03:54,854 --> 00:03:55,985
That’s it, isn’t it?

53
00:03:56,829 --> 00:04:00,679
That’s why your heart’s not totally in to finding a great band for the end of the school year.

54
00:04:01,146 --> 00:04:02,273
Haley and Nathan.

55
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,267
Yeah. That, and-

56
00:04:07,618 --> 00:04:08,489
Jake.

57
00:04:09,482 --> 00:04:11,529
You’ve been calling my attorneys a lot.

58
00:04:12,073 --> 00:04:13,279
I thought I could help.

59
00:04:13,368 --> 00:04:15,282
Well, you just pissed them off.

60
00:04:17,468 --> 00:04:19,609
There are two tragedy’s in life:-

61
00:04:20,157 --> 00:04:22,692
one is to lose your heart’s desire.

62
00:04:23,189 --> 00:04:25,134
The other is to gain it.

63
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:30,218
Now the little that Shaw realised at the time that his words would be the basis of your final.

64
00:04:30,883 --> 00:04:34,974
I’d like you to write an essay on the meaning of Shaw’s quote.

65
00:04:35,266 --> 00:04:37,288
It’s due on Monday...

66
00:04:37,392 --> 00:04:39,521
and then your school year will be over.

67
00:04:48,451 --> 00:04:51,133
I guess Haley’s not coming back after all, huh?

68
00:05:03,263 --> 00:05:04,277
Game to eleven?

69
00:05:05,142 --> 00:05:06,550
I’ll give you ten and the ball.

70
00:05:09,521 --> 00:05:10,370
Game.

71
00:05:11,327 --> 00:05:12,131
See?

72
00:05:13,293 --> 00:05:14,650
You’ll be back in no time.

73
00:05:14,788 --> 00:05:17,020
Shooting weak-ass jump shots: that’s your game.

74
00:05:17,716 --> 00:05:19,473
I can hardly jump, man.

75
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:22,745
Look, I know you don’t wanna hear this, but if you blow off this English final,

76
00:05:22,811 --> 00:05:26,892
you’re not gonna even be eligible to shoot the... ‘weak-ass jump shots’.

77
00:05:29,529 --> 00:05:32,120
It’s about loss. I can help you if you want.

78
00:05:33,558 --> 00:05:35,207
You don’t think I can write about loss?

79
00:05:41,872 --> 00:05:43,086
Hey sexy!

80
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,288
What’s wrong?

81
00:05:45,646 --> 00:05:48,566
I’m dead. I tanked my calculus final.

82
00:05:48,745 --> 00:05:50,786
Are you sure? Maybe you did okay.

83
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:53,947
Erica, we hung out all week and I was totally unprepared.

84
00:05:54,263 --> 00:05:57,079
And you can’t exactly bluff your way through math, you know?

85
00:05:58,365 --> 00:06:00,351
God, my parents are gonna kill me.

86
00:06:04,673 --> 00:06:05,241
Hey.

87
00:06:06,219 --> 00:06:06,797
Hey.

88
00:06:07,964 --> 00:06:09,787
You wanna go on a road trip this weekend?

89
00:06:10,376 --> 00:06:11,396
Okay, where?

90
00:06:11,636 --> 00:06:13,367
New York, to see Haley.

91
00:06:13,982 --> 00:06:17,452
Alright, odd I know, coming from me, but we do have finals.

92
00:06:17,607 --> 00:06:18,451
The essay.

93
00:06:18,768 --> 00:06:22,823
I’ll bring my laptop. Whoever sits shotgun can do the typing; whaddaya say, huh?

94
00:06:24,237 --> 00:06:25,399
And why Haley?

95
00:06:25,757 --> 00:06:26,627
Why now?

96
00:06:26,796 --> 00:06:28,219
Because we started the year together...

97
00:06:29,070 --> 00:06:31,087
and I can’t end it without seeing her.

98
00:06:37,169 --> 00:06:39,746
Okay. I’ll go, we can talk.

99
00:06:39,821 --> 00:06:40,805
We need to talk.

100
00:06:41,112 --> 00:06:42,065
What’s wrong?

101
00:06:42,622 --> 00:06:46,186
Well, I don’t want you to be alarmed, but, my mother took a spill in New Zealand.

102
00:06:47,168 --> 00:06:48,551
That’s terrible.

103
00:06:49,386 --> 00:06:50,687
She’s asked me to come home.

104
00:06:51,286 --> 00:06:52,452
Well, you have to.

105
00:06:54,536 --> 00:06:57,348
And I don’t know how long for, coz there’s a bit more to it.

106
00:07:02,970 --> 00:07:05,160
I may have a problem coming back into the States;

107
00:07:05,934 --> 00:07:08,601
I’m not a citizen and, well,

108
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,872
Dan’s trying to get me deported.

109
00:07:16,410 --> 00:07:17,300
Deported?!

110
00:07:17,694 --> 00:07:18,964
What is wrong with you?!

111
00:07:19,328 --> 00:07:21,556
Why can't you simply stay out of my life?!

112
00:07:21,831 --> 00:07:22,891
Why can’t you?

113
00:07:22,963 --> 00:07:26,710
Oh, please, I’ve been ignoring you for the last seventeen years!

114
00:07:26,784 --> 00:07:27,607
Have you?

115
00:07:28,695 --> 00:07:31,093
Coz you’ve been coming around quite a bit, Karen.

116
00:07:31,595 --> 00:07:33,808
I mean, with all your anger and outrage.

117
00:07:34,657 --> 00:07:35,917
Some would call it...

118
00:07:37,161 --> 00:07:38,036
passion.

119
00:07:38,401 --> 00:07:39,768
Don’t flatter yourself.

120
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:42,148
Just back off Andy and Lucas.

121
00:07:42,214 --> 00:07:43,668
And leave my world alone.

122
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,108
Isn’t that what this is really about?

123
00:07:51,856 --> 00:07:52,593
God!

124
00:08:10,461 --> 00:08:13,068
Next time... that’ll be your face!

125
00:08:21,301 --> 00:08:22,991
You guys ready for the summer?

126
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:27,816
Yeah, me too.

127
00:08:27,998 --> 00:08:32,125
But, first, let’s give it up for the girl who made this happen tonight;

128
00:08:32,186 --> 00:08:34,716
my bestest friend: Peyton Sawyer.

129
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:41,438
Peyton, Peyton, Peyton...

130
00:08:50,218 --> 00:08:51,079
Jake...

131
00:08:52,027 --> 00:08:53,889
You’ve been calling my attorneys a lot.

132
00:08:54,770 --> 00:08:55,857
I thought I could help.

133
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,890
Well, you just pissed them off...

134
00:09:00,275 --> 00:09:01,268
at first.

135
00:09:02,645 --> 00:09:06,505
Then, you clearly weren’t going away, so they went over Nikki’s testimony line by line.

136
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:08,666
And they found something.

137
00:09:09,793 --> 00:09:10,960
She lied, Peyton.

138
00:09:11,686 --> 00:09:14,693
She said that she’d been away at college but she wasn’t.

139
00:09:14,764 --> 00:09:16,229
She hadn’t been there in months.

140
00:09:16,398 --> 00:09:19,506
Well does, does that even matter, you know? Is that enough?

141
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,775
Yeah, any lie is a lie under oath.

142
00:09:21,876 --> 00:09:24,135
Once my attorneys get a hold of her transcripts,

143
00:09:24,467 --> 00:09:26,071
the judge is gonna lift the court order;

144
00:09:26,141 --> 00:09:29,095
I’ll have sole custody of Jenny for a new hearing.

145
00:09:29,178 --> 00:09:31,471
And a chance to testify against all her other lies.

146
00:09:31,861 --> 00:09:34,978
That’s... that’s so great, Jake.

147
00:09:37,461 --> 00:09:38,685
When d’ya get out?

148
00:09:38,839 --> 00:09:40,199
A day or so, probably.

149
00:09:40,784 --> 00:09:42,730
And I’m gonna come find you as soon as I do.

150
00:09:43,856 --> 00:09:45,213
You did this, Peyton.

151
00:09:45,884 --> 00:09:49,201
You’ve given me hope; and I love you so much for it.

152
00:09:50,801 --> 00:09:52,914
Hey, hey, come on, don’t cry.

153
00:09:53,155 --> 00:09:55,423
Haven’t you ever cried when your happy?

154
00:10:08,213 --> 00:10:09,277
Come in, Nathan.

155
00:10:10,801 --> 00:10:11,986
How’d you know it was me?

156
00:10:12,293 --> 00:10:14,055
I can smell the confusion.

157
00:10:17,404 --> 00:10:19,205
That was a joke by the way.

158
00:10:20,793 --> 00:10:23,230
Nobody ever laughs at my jokes.

159
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:24,919
That’s coz they’re not funny, Coach.

160
00:10:26,522 --> 00:10:29,246
Little bird told me you were moving back home.

161
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,955
That little bird’s name Lucas?

162
00:10:32,953 --> 00:10:34,105
He cares about you.

163
00:10:35,973 --> 00:10:36,972
So do I.

164
00:10:38,774 --> 00:10:41,077
You’ve come quite a distance this year.

165
00:10:42,588 --> 00:10:45,460
I think moving out of that house has been good for you.

166
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:46,608
Coach.

167
00:10:47,407 --> 00:10:48,169
Look at me.

168
00:10:48,985 --> 00:10:49,798
I’m a mess.

169
00:10:50,724 --> 00:10:52,803
Nah, you’re just a little bit broken.

170
00:10:53,632 --> 00:10:56,914
But it’s nothing that a summer at High Flyers couldn’t fix.

171
00:10:57,022 --> 00:10:59,048
- Could’ve fixed. 
- Still can.

172
00:10:59,489 --> 00:11:02,306
Dan Scott’s not the only one with pull in this town.

173
00:11:03,114 --> 00:11:07,524
The only thing that held you back as a player last season was heart...

174
00:11:08,218 --> 00:11:11,370
and I’ve watched that change over the past year.

175
00:11:12,330 --> 00:11:14,221
And I’ve been so proud of you.

176
00:11:17,487 --> 00:11:20,753
That camp has world class trainers.

177
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:23,600
They can mend the physical part.

178
00:11:24,615 --> 00:11:26,881
I have a hunch, once that happens,

179
00:11:27,569 --> 00:11:29,370
the game will heal your heart.

180
00:11:31,116 --> 00:11:32,289
I dreamt about it;

181
00:11:32,954 --> 00:11:33,927
in the hospital...

182
00:11:34,517 --> 00:11:36,021
about going to that camp.

183
00:11:37,475 --> 00:11:38,366
I don’t know.

184
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:41,808
My mom’s coming home soon.

185
00:11:42,878 --> 00:11:44,122
Gotta think about it.

186
00:11:48,069 --> 00:11:49,788
Promise me you’ll do that.

187
00:12:04,786 --> 00:12:07,909
How great is this? Dinner together, steaks on the grill.

188
00:12:07,976 --> 00:12:09,020
You not punching me.

189
00:12:12,005 --> 00:12:13,638
So I got some good news today.

190
00:12:13,731 --> 00:12:14,631
What’s that?

191
00:12:15,093 --> 00:12:17,171
Whitey thinks he can get me back into High Flyers.

192
00:12:19,193 --> 00:12:21,897
Well, as much as I love hearing you talk about basketball again,

193
00:12:22,496 --> 00:12:24,636
I really don’t think camp’s a smart play for you right now.

194
00:12:24,892 --> 00:12:27,412
- Dad, its High Flyers. 
- Exactly my point.

195
00:12:27,693 --> 00:12:30,555
You’re injured Nathan. You don’t want the scouts to see you like that.

196
00:12:30,707 --> 00:12:32,285
Plus, there’s your mother to consider.

197
00:12:34,221 --> 00:12:36,187
Listen, I don’t like to burden you with these things

198
00:12:36,234 --> 00:12:38,266
but you’re a man so I’m gonna be honest with you.

199
00:12:39,807 --> 00:12:42,832
Your mother’s pill addiction started when you moved out.

200
00:12:44,948 --> 00:12:47,048
Now, in no way does that mean you’re to blame, coz you’re not.

201
00:12:47,139 --> 00:12:50,606
But... she’s gonna be vulnerable when she comes home.

202
00:12:50,816 --> 00:12:52,709
And she’s gonna need you more than ever.

203
00:12:58,982 --> 00:13:03,068
Okay, guys, as student council president, I have one final duty

204
00:13:03,113 --> 00:13:04,849
before the summer begins and this is it.

205
00:13:04,925 --> 00:13:07,966
Tree Hill High, school is out and it is time to party!

206
00:13:08,065 --> 00:13:10,477
Please welcome Jimmy Eat World!

207
00:14:10,304 --> 00:14:11,313
So, it’s kinda weird;

208
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:13,981
us... living under the same roof.

209
00:14:15,101 --> 00:14:16,233
Isn’t that weird.

210
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:18,337
Yes it is.

211
00:14:18,756 --> 00:14:21,670
I mean, who would have thought this could have happened back when...

212
00:14:22,253 --> 00:14:23,272
we were together?

213
00:14:28,669 --> 00:14:30,619
You been talking to Peyton much?

214
00:14:31,076 --> 00:14:32,039
Little bit.

215
00:14:33,492 --> 00:14:35,530
I wish I was in her life more, you know?

216
00:14:38,635 --> 00:14:41,813
Guess I know what loss you’ll be writing about for your essay.

217
00:14:43,104 --> 00:14:45,073
I lost myself this year, Brooke.

218
00:14:46,272 --> 00:14:49,415
And what I did, I lost the people I truly care about.

219
00:14:51,321 --> 00:14:52,554
Oh, by the way, um...

220
00:14:53,763 --> 00:14:55,309
when we get to New York...

221
00:14:55,852 --> 00:14:58,653
I hope you’ll understand if we spend most of our time with Haley.

222
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:02,738
It’s just... important that I focus on her today.

223
00:15:03,358 --> 00:15:04,095
You know?

224
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:05,697
Of course.

225
00:15:07,575 --> 00:15:09,133
Everything else can wait.

226
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:30,096
Lucas!

227
00:16:31,785 --> 00:16:34,024
Oh my gosh! Hi.

228
00:16:34,112 --> 00:16:38,196
Oh, well, it’s about time the tribal leaders came to collect their squaw.

229
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,528
Oh, shut up, Chris.

230
00:16:39,886 --> 00:16:42,077
Yeah, shut up, Chris.

231
00:16:42,226 --> 00:16:43,336
Alright, I’m going.

232
00:16:45,723 --> 00:16:48,729
Oh... I see you couldn’t stay away from me.

233
00:16:48,831 --> 00:16:49,700
Out!

234
00:16:51,325 --> 00:16:54,452
I’m sorry. Oh, it’s good to see you too, Brooke.

235
00:16:55,292 --> 00:16:57,515
Yeah, you too, fugitive girl.

236
00:16:58,533 --> 00:17:00,002
Well, so what’re you guys doing here?

237
00:17:00,095 --> 00:17:01,758
We bought your English assignment.

238
00:17:01,837 --> 00:17:04,069
My- Oh my gosh, finals!

239
00:17:04,154 --> 00:17:06,423
Oh, god, that just feels like a totally different life.

240
00:17:07,390 --> 00:17:08,440
Let’s go, diva.

241
00:17:08,702 --> 00:17:11,870
Hey, Joey D, this is my friend Lucas and my friend Brooke.

242
00:17:11,952 --> 00:17:13,909
What’s up, guys? Ah, sorry I gotta drag her away

243
00:17:13,971 --> 00:17:16,515
but we’ve got three meetings and a satellite radio interview.

244
00:17:16,592 --> 00:17:17,907
- You ready? 
- Um...

245
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:23,364
I’m just feeling a little... flu... ish.

246
00:17:23,677 --> 00:17:24,409
Haley...

247
00:17:24,518 --> 00:17:25,234
Yeah, I-

248
00:17:26,790 --> 00:17:28,552
It’s totally going around.

249
00:17:31,174 --> 00:17:32,223
Cover for me?

250
00:17:32,372 --> 00:17:34,758
Really, because I’m just, I’m sick as a dog here.

251
00:17:34,942 --> 00:17:37,191
No, no, wait Haley, no, no, wait... guys?

252
00:17:38,069 --> 00:17:39,140
I’m gonna be sick

253
00:17:39,509 --> 00:17:40,507
It’ll be okay.

254
00:17:40,799 --> 00:17:42,489
Dan can’t actually affect me legally.

255
00:17:42,626 --> 00:17:44,746
Yeah, but if you leave the country, then-

256
00:17:44,844 --> 00:17:48,842
Yes, it could create a bit of red tape that would hold up my return to the states.

257
00:17:52,401 --> 00:17:53,549
I’m gonna miss you.

258
00:17:55,110 --> 00:17:56,507
